Stress-test E4: map of (+0) is identity over [4][32].

Cryptol property:
    \(xs : [4][32]) -> map (\x -> x + 0) xs == xs

Emitted structure:
  foldr (ite _ _ false) true
    (gen 4 (fun i => bvEq (at (gen 4 (fun i' => bvAdd xs[i'] 0)) i) xs[i]))
  = true

Discharge (8 lines):
  1. simp only [bvAdd_id_r]        -- remove the `+0`
  2. rw [gen_atWithDefault]         -- gen-after-at round-trip collapses
  3. hgen : ∀i, bvEq xs[i] xs[i] = true
  4. simp only [hgen]               -- rewrite each fold element to true
  5. decide                         -- fold of all-trues at size 4

Findings:
- simp can't apply bvEq_refl directly under a universal fold
  (RHS has metavariable a). Had to construct a hand-quantified
  `hgen` to make simp rewrite pointwise.
- `decide` closes small concrete folds over Bool.
